properties.Name: DunBradstreetUccFiling
properties.Description:
A legal document creditors use to secure their rights to collateral specified in a secured financing agreement. 

This document, which the creditor files with the appropriate state authority (Secretary of State office), gives the creditor a legally recognized interest in the collateral until payment is received in full. It also provides legal title to these assets in the event a debtor suffers financial hardship and is unable to meet its promise to pay.

Columns.Name: DunsNumber
Columns.Description: Dun & Bradstreet (D&B) provides a D-U-N-S Number, a unique nine digit identification number, for each physical location of your business.

Columns.Name: ReportPurchaseDate
Columns.Description: The purchase date of the report.

Columns.Name: FiledDate
Columns.Description: The date that the UCC filing was filed.

Columns.Name: SecuredPartyName
Columns.Description: The name of the secured party.

Columns.Name: SecuredPartyCity
Columns.Description: The 'city' component of the secured party address.

Columns.Name: SecuredPartyState
Columns.Description: The 'state' component of the secured party address.

Columns.Name: DebtorPartyName
Columns.Description: The name of the debtor party.

Columns.Name: DebtorPartyCity
Columns.Description: The 'city' component of the debtor party address.

Columns.Name: DebtorPartyState
Columns.Description: The state' component of the debtor party address.

Columns.Name: FiledWithName
Columns.Description: The name with whom the UCC filing was filed.

Columns.Name: FiledAtCity
Columns.Description: The 'city' component of the UCC filing was filed at.

Columns.Name: FiledAtState
Columns.Description: The 'state' component of the UCC filing was filed at.

Columns.Name: CollateralDescription
Columns.Description:
The description of the collateral.

Ex:
- Leased equipment
- Leased Unspecified

Columns.Name: DunBradstreetUccFilingTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Dun Bradstreet UCC Filing Type.
